stanford pan asian music festival elegant gathering ii arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe calendar stanford pan asian music festival elegant gathering ii friday february 10 2012 12 00pm campbell recital hall free lectures and demonstrations associated with the eighth annual pan asian music festival take the format of elegant gatherings an ancient term used to describe a gathering of scholars and artists join professor yosihiko tokumaru as he presents a lecture entitled quotation and intertextuality in japanese music with a musical demonstration by master tosiko yonekawa ii followed by a japanese omotesenke tea ceremony performed by professor terumi takahashi presented in collaboration with the center for east asian studies at stanford sponsored by department of music click for more information home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
